crucial for the production of mushrooms with better flavor, appearance, texture, nutritional qualities, and medicinal properties at low cost. Mushroom culture is a biotechnological process that recycles ligninocellulosic wastes, since mushrooms are food for human consumption and the spent substrate can be used in different ways.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Sánchez","given":"Carmen","literal":""},{"family":"Sánchez","given":"Carmen","literal":""}],"citation-key":"sanchez_modern_2004","year":"2004","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Modern aspects of mushroom culture technology"],"author-links":["[[Author/Carmen Sánchez]]","[[Author/Carmen Sánchez]]"],"attachment":["[[biblib/sanchez_modern_2004/sanchez_modern_2004.pdf|PDF]]"],"related":[[]]},"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"last_embed":{"hash":"1b10l6i","at":1774951894932}},"smart_blocks:Research/@sanchez_modern_2004.md#---frontmatter---": {"path":null,"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[0.01183065,0.02233695,0.05855366,-0.01976185,0.08104256,-0.02482931,-0.01023887,0.04048987,-0.05675876,-0.00079518,-0.00588988,-0.05621032,0.00471243,-0.0022199,0.04551406,0.05619334,0.01287192,-0.00805267,0.00624127,-0.00021459,0.0658751,-0.00086448,0.005847,0.02388434,0.02543942,-0.00612362,-0.04177195,-0.02573524,-0.02598196,-0.215114,-0.02510781,0.07629378,0.02862001,-0.03335271,-0.00537288,-0.02600164,0.01947545,-0.0589345,-0.0135326,0.05595748,0.01519316,0.04151853,-0.04987277,0.00758636,-0.03247443,-0.00197843,-0.04641197,0.00277149,-0.00419182,-0.08152733,-0.02837674,-0.06799607,0.03121053,-0.02905761,0.02368291,0.00377428,0.03129257,0.00335035,0.02367374,0.03188341,0.08373014,0.01060446,-0.19432607,0.06530738,0.04453587,-0.01003769,-0.10442747,0.02539079,0.07171731,0.00623522,-0.08869872,0.01536329,0.06212559,0.03232718,0.06937447,0.0016177,0.01257256,-0.07113949,-0.07429462,-0.00805484,0.01001871,0.06431372,0.00305575,-0.01387282,-0.05778737,-0.0